Munodawafa is the third senior government official to be detained by the Anti-Corruption Commission. Environment and Tourism Minister Prisca Mupfumira appeared in court last week on corruption charges involving $95 million, while former Director of State Residences Douglas Tapfuma was arrested on Tuesday.  1 Phone calls to the commission’s executive secretary, Silence Pondo, for comment weren’t answered. To contact the reporter on this story:
